data.enText: to hit sb/sth with great force

data.chText: 雨点猛烈地打在窗户上。
data.enText: The rain lashed at the windows.
Huge waves lashed the shore.
to hit a person or an animal with a whip , rope, stick, etc.
to criticize sb/sth in a very angry way
to fasten sth tightly to sth else with ropes

data.chText: 几根原木捆扎在一起做成了木筏。
data.enText: Several logs had been lashed together to make a raft.

data.chText: 暴风雨中甲板上所有的东西都必须系牢。
data.enText: During the storm everything on deck had to be lashed down.
to move or to move sth quickly and violently from side to side

data.chText: 鳄鱼的尾巴在急速地左右甩动。
data.enText: The crocodile's tail was lashing furiously from side to side.

to suddenly try to hit sb

data.chText: 她突然狠狠地打那个男孩。
data.enText: She suddenly lashed out at the boy.
to criticize sb in an angry way

data.chText: 他写了一篇尖刻的文章，猛烈抨击批评他的人。
data.enText: In a bitter article he lashed out at his critics.

data.enText: They each received 20 lashes for stealing.

data.enText: to feel the lash of sb's tongue (= to be spoken to in an angry and critical way)

data.text: beat ♦ batter ♦ pound ♦ pummel ♦ lash ♦ hammer

data.chText: 以上各词均含反复敲打之义，尤指使劲地击打。
data.enText: All these words mean to hit sb/sth many times, especially hard.
beat
to hit sb/sth a lot of times, especially very hard
Someone was beating at the door.

data.chText: 昨天夜里有人发现一名小伙子被打死了。
data.enText: A young man was found beaten to death last night.

data.chText: 那时候，孩子们常常因为很小的过错而挨打。
data.enText: At that time, children were often beaten for quite minor offences (= as a punishment) .
batter

data.chText: 指连续猛击，尤指殴打致伤或造成破坏：
data.enText: to hit sb/sth hard a lot of times, especially in a way that causes serious damage
He had been badly battered around the head and face.
Severe winds have been battering the coast.
pound

data.chText: 指连续猛击，尤指发出砰砰的撞击声：
data.enText: to hit sb/sth hard a lot of times, especially in a way that makes a lot of noise

data.chText: 暴雨砰砰砰地砸在屋顶上。
data.enText: Heavy rain pounded on the roof.
pummel
to hit sb/sth a lot of times, especially with your fists (= tightly closed hands)
lash
to hit sb/sth with a lot of force

data.chText: 雨点猛烈地打在窗户上。
data.enText: The rain lashed at the window.
The subject of lash is often rain , wind , hail , sea or waves .
hammer

data.chText: 指大声、猛烈地反复敲打、连续击打：
data.enText: to hit sb/sth hard a lot of times, in a way that is noisy or violent
He hammered the door with his fists.

data.chText: 这两个词意思差别不大，但pound有时指较匀速而稳定地击打；hammer更猛烈，且常用于比喻。
data.enText: There is not much difference in meaning between these two, but to pound is sometimes a steadier action. To hammer can be more violent and it is often used figuratively.

trans: （用武器或手脚）迅猛攻击，殴打

tr: a quick blow delivered with a whip or whiplike object
example: the whip raised a red welt

tr: leather strip that forms the flexible part of a whip
any of the short curved hairs that grow from the edges of the eyelids
bind with a rope, chain, or cord
beat severely with a whip or rod
example: The teacher often flogged the students

value.def: Your lashes are the hairs that grow on the edge of your upper and lower eyelids.

example.ex: ...sombre grey eyes, with unusually long lashes...
example.tran: 一双忧郁的灰眼睛，眼睫毛长得出奇

example.ex: Joanna studied him through her lashes.
example.tran: 乔安娜眯着眼睛打量他。

value.def: If you lash two or more things together, you tie one of them firmly to the other.

example.ex: Secure the anchor by lashing it to the rail...
The shelter is built by lashing poles together to form a small dome...
example.tran: 把杆子扎成一个穹顶小棚就成了遮蔽所。
辛迪把她的快艇系在旁边。

example.ex: We were worried about the lifeboat which was not lashed down.
example.tran: 我们为那艘没有系牢的救生艇悬着心。

value.def: If wind, rain, or water lashes someone or something, it hits them violently.

example.ex: The worst winter storms of the century lashed the east coast of North America...
example.tran: 本世纪最恶劣的冬季暴风雪横扫北美东海岸。

example.ex: Suddenly rain lashed against the windows...
example.tran: 蓦地，大雨猛烈地抽打在窗户上。

example.ex: The rain was absolutely lashing down.

value.def: If someone lashes you or lashes into you, they speak very angrily to you, criticizing you or saying you have done something wrong.

example.ex: She went quiet for a moment while she summoned up the words to lash him...
example.tran: 她沉默片刻，寻思着抨击他的话语。

example.ex: The report lashes into police commanders for failing to act on intelligence information.
example.tran: 该报告严斥警局指挥官没有根据情报采取行动。

example.ex: Never before had he felt the full lash of John's temper.
example.tran: 他以前从未见识过约翰如此暴烈的脾气。

value.def: A lash is a thin strip of leather at the end of a whip.
A lash is a blow with a whip, especially a blow on someone's back as a punishment.

example.ex: The villagers sentenced one man to five lashes for stealing a ham from his neighbor.
example.tran: 村民们裁定将一名偷邻居火腿的男子鞭打5下。

value.tran: （尤指作为惩罚抽在背部的）鞭打

value.def: If someone lashes another person, they hit that person with a whip.

example.ex: They snatched up whips and lashed the backs of those who had fallen.
example.tran: 他们抓起鞭子，朝跌倒的人背上抽去。

value.def: If an animal lashes its tail, or if its tail lashes, it moves its tail very fast and violently.

example.ex: When in danger, the anteater lashes its tail round a branch...
example.tran: 遇有危险，食蚁兽会迅速用尾巴卷住树枝。

example.ex: They tried to get the harpoon into the ray before the sting tail came lashing over to retaliate...
example.tran: 他们试图把鱼叉刺进鳐鱼体内，以防它猛摆那蜇人的尾巴报复。

example.ex: Don't go near that lashing tail.

trans: （用武器或手脚）迅猛攻击，殴打
